## 4. Seat Capacity Enforcement Flow

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[School Admin Action] --> B{Operation Type}
    B -->|Add Student| C[Check Capacity]
    B -->|Bulk Import| D[Check Capacity x N]
    B -->|Upgrade Tier| E[Update Limits]

    C --> F[GET /api/school-admin/capacity]
    F --> G[Return current usage]
    G --> H{Capacity Available?}

    H -->|Yes| I[Proceed with operation]
    H -->|No| J[Return 409 Error<br/>Seat limit exceeded]

    D --> K[Calculate total students]
    K --> L{Total <= maxStudents?}

    L -->|Yes| M[Proceed with import]
    L -->|No| N[Return 409 Error<br/>Would exceed limit]

    E --> O[Update schools.subscriptionTier]
    O --> P[Update schools.maxStudents]
    P --> Q[New capacity active]

    I --> R[Create student record]
    M --> S[Bulk create students]

    R --> T[Increment usage count]
    S --> T

    style C fill:#fef3c7
    style J fill:#f8d7da
    style M fill:#d4edda
    style N fill:#f8d7da
    style R fill:#d4edda
    style T fill:#c3e6cb
```

**API Endpoints:**
- `GET /api/school-admin/capacity` - Check capacity
- `POST /api/school-admin/students` - Add student (with check)
- `POST /api/school-admin/students/bulk-import` - Bulk import (with check)
- `PATCH /api/admin/schools/[id]/tier` - Upgrade tier

**Capacity Limits by Tier:**
| Tier | Max Students |
|------|--------------|
| Free | 50 |
| Basic | 100 |
| Standard | 500 |
| Premium | 1000 |
| Enterprise | 10000 |

