## 6. Library Book Circulation Flow

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[Student/Teacher] --> B[GET /api/library/books]
    B --> C[View available books]

    C --> D{Request to Borrow}
    D --> E[POST /api/library/issue]

    E --> F[Check: available_copies > 0?]
    F -->|No| G[Return error: Unavailable]
    F -->|Yes| H[CREATE circulation record<br/>status: issued]

    H --> I[Decrement books.available_copies]
    I --> J[Increment books.currently_borrowed]
    J --> K[Set dueDate = today + 14 days]

    K --> L[Book issued successfully]

    L --> M{Student Returns Book}
    M --> N[POST /api/library/issue/:id/return]

    N --> O[Update circulation.status: returned]
    O --> P[Set returnDate]
    P --> Q[Increment books.available_copies]

    Q --> R{Overdue?}
    R -->|Yes| S[Calculate fine]
    R -->|No| T[No fine]

    S --> U[CREATE fine_payment record]
    T --> V[Return complete]
    U --> V

    style A fill:#8b5cf6
    style H fill:#d4edda
    style L fill:#c3e6cb
    style O fill:#d4edda
    style S fill:#fff3cd
    style V fill:#c3e6cb
```

**API Endpoints:**
- `GET /api/library/books` - List books
- `POST /api/library/issue` - Issue book
- `POST /api/library/issue/:id/return` - Return book
- `POST /api/library/fines` - Pay fine
- `GET /api/library/members` - List members

**Database Tables:**
1. `books` - Book catalog
2. `circulation` - Checkout tracking
3. `library_members` - Member records
4. `fine_payments` - Fine payments
5. `reservations` - Book holds

