## 9. Student Journal Flow (JSONB Pattern)

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[Student] --> B[Open Journal Page]
    B --> C[GET /api/journal]

    C --> D[Extract from users.settings]
    D --> E["Parse: settings.journalEntries[]"]
    E --> F[Return entries array]

    F --> G{Student Action}

    G -->|New Entry| H[Click New Entry]
    H --> I[Check: Entry for today exists?]
    I -->|Yes| J[Disable button: One per day]
    I -->|No| K[Show form]

    K --> L[POST /api/journal]
    L --> M["Validate: { date, title, content, mood, tags }"]
    M --> N[Parse existing journalEntries]
    N --> O["Push: { id, date, title, content, mood, tags, createdAt }"]
    O --> P["UPDATE users.settings = { ...settings, journalEntries }"]
    P --> Q[Return new entry]

    G -->|Edit| R[Click entry]
    R --> S[PUT /api/journal/[id]]
    S --> T["Find entry: journalEntries.find(e => e.id === id)"]
    T --> U["Update: { title, content, mood, tags, updatedAt }"]
    U --> V[UPDATE users.settings]
    V --> W[Return updated entry]

    G -->|Delete| X[Click delete]
    X --> Y[DELETE /api/journal/[id]]
    Y --> Z["Filter: journalEntries.filter(e => e.id !== id)"]
    Z --> AA[UPDATE users.settings]
    AA --> AB[Return success]

    style D fill:#9c27b0
    style E fill:#f3e5f5
    style P fill:#d4edda
    style J fill:#fff3cd
    style Q fill:#c3e6cb
```

**API Endpoints:**
- `GET /api/journal` - Get all entries
- `POST /api/journal` - Create entry (1/day limit)
- `GET /api/journal/[id]` - Get single entry
- `PUT /api/journal/[id]` - Update entry
- `DELETE /api/journal/[id]` - Delete entry

**Storage Pattern:**
```typescript
// users.settings (JSONB)
{
  journalEntries: [
    {
      id: "uuid",
      date: "2026-03-05",
      title: "My Day",
      content: "Today was...",
      mood: "happy",
      tags: ["school", "friends"],
      createdAt: "2026-03-05T10:00:00Z",
      updatedAt: "2026-03-05T10:00:00Z"
    }
  ]
}
```

