## 14. JSONB vs Table Storage Pattern

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph "TABLE STORAGE PATTERN<br/>(Leave Requests)"
        direction TB
        T1["Separate table: leave_requests"]
        T2["Columns: id, type, status, dates..."]
        T3["Indexed: applicantId, status, dates"]
        T4["Query: db.select().from(leave_requests)"]

        T1 --> T2 --> T3 --> T4
    end

    subgraph "JSONB STORAGE PATTERN<br/>(Journal Entries)"
        direction TB
        J1["User table: users"]
        J2["Column: settings (JSONB)"]
        J3["Structure: settings.journalEntries[]"]
        J4["Query: Extract from JSONB in code"]

        J1 --> J2 --> J3 --> J4
    end

    subgraph "WHEN TO USE"
        W1["Table Pattern:<br/>- Complex queries<br/>- Foreign keys<br/>- Indexing needed<br/>- Multi-user access"]
        W2["JSONB Pattern:<br/>- User-scoped data<br/>- Simple CRUD<br/>- Flexible schema<br/>- One-to-user relation"]
    end

    style T1 fill:#10b981,color:#fff
    style J1 fill:#9c27b0,color:#fff
```

